therapy, that's treating the cancer, but it might have side effects.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050205,0.096108,0.1035,0.096364,0.091844,0.089588,0.091533,0.087215,0.084542,0.085953,0.069748,0.053396],"unified_progress":[0.093635,0.12218,0.10121,0.092108,0.087601,0.087071,0.080699,0.085445,0.075452,0.068999,0.058987,0.046608]},{"section":11,"text":"The physical exam shows crackles, which are fine inspiratory crackles, often heard in the lungs.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.055477,0.087238,0.094616,0.10664,0.099488,0.098193,0.096034,0.088506,0.078863,0.070901,0.065409,0.058634],"unified_progress":[0.065176,0.09464,0.097678,0.10147,0.098707,0.095351,0.088863,0.086176,0.087308,0.070435,0.061194,0.053008]},{"section":12,"text":"Crackles can be due to interstitial lung disease (like pulmonary fibrosis) or maybe a lower respiratory infection, but given the context of cancer and chemotherapy, it's more likely related to the treatment.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038258,0.066108,0.088664,0.10665,0.10191,0.099752,0.10371,0.095175,0.087414,0.088588,0.068847,0.054924],"unified_progress":[0.038746,0.07362,0.093695,0.10653,0.10356,0.099768,0.10261,0.096375,0.089827,0.082917,0.066218,0.046134]},{"section":13,"text":"Clubbing in the fingers is another clue.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050616,0.080464,0.088133,0.095323,0.096351,0.096481,0.096713,0.091413,0.085099,0.079408,0.073628,0.066371],"unified_progress":[0.053736,0.081879,0.090027,0.095564,0.098041,0.096411,0.093736,0.091631,0.087137,0.079595,0.070948,0.061295]},{"section":14,"text":"Clubbing is often associated with hypoxia, which can be due to chronic lung disease or right-to-left shunts, like in congenital heart defects or Eisenstein's anomaly.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036537,0.058634,0.079346,0.093243,0.1005,0.10397,0.10633,0.10